faction /ˈfækʃən/

(factions) 

1. N-COUNT A faction is an organized group of people within a larger group, which opposes some of the ideas of the larger group and fights for its own ideas. 派系 

例： A peace agreement will be signed by the leaders of the country's warring factions. 一项和平协议将由该国交战各派领导们签署。 

2. N a television programme, film, or literary work comprising a dramatized presentation of actual events (电视、电影、文学等的)纪实

